arrived at the break of day at the top of the mountain, and po&s;&s;e&s;&s;|ed
them&s;elves of that advantageous po&s;t.</P>
<P>The Greeks were &s;oon appri&s;ed of this mi&s;|fortune, and
Leonidas &s;eeing that his po&s;t was no longer tenable, advi&s;ed the troops
of his allies to retire, and re&s;erve them&s;elves for bet|ter times, and the
