<PB N="148" REF="151"> native &s;eats to undergo all the vici&s;&s;itudes and
dangers of the &s;ea, to implore a retreat from fo|reign &s;tates, and give up
their native lands to the &s;poiler was a mo&s;t moving &s;pectacle. Yet the
&s;tea|dine&s;s and courage of &s;ome, and the pious re&s;ig|nation of all,
demanded the utmo&s;t admiration. The young and adventurous embarked for
